vim /lib/systemd/system/docker.service
Line:14 change to: ExecStart=/usr/bin/dockerd -H tcp://0.0.0.0:4243 -H unix:///var/run/docker.sock
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo service docker restart

Checking connectivity:
curl http://localhost:4243/version
Also check this:
curl http://54.221.134.7:4243/version

*** 4243 is docker API port.
*** Docker host ports range: (32768-60999)
NOTE: Need to Allow these port ranges.

*Build Docker image using Dockerfile:
* vim Dockerfile
  Copy Paste code Dockerfile code.

* docker build -t image:v1 .
* docker images(you can see image created)

*Push docker image to docker registry:
docker login
username: give it.
password: give it.
docker tag YOUR_IMAGE USERNAME/REPO_NAME
docker push USERNAME/REPO_NAME
